esource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The beds\", \"from\": 1474, \"to\": 1482}, {\"ngram\": \"scrutiny\", \"from\": 1504, \"to\": 1512}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1518, \"to\": 1526}, {\"ngram\": \"viewers\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1538}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2020 Olympics\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1596}, {\"ngram\": \"many Olympic athletes\", \"from\": 1616, \"to\": 1637}, {\"ngram\": \"social media\", \"from\": 1646, \"to\": 1658}, {\"ngram\": \"viewers\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1674}, {\"ngram\": \"the beds\", \"from\": 1680, \"to\": 1688}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The bed in the video has since been recycled,\\\" Israeli baseball player Ben Wanger said in a since-deleted TikTok video showing him and eight of his teammates jumping on a bed to disprove the viral rumor that the Olympic committee had chosen the cardboard sleeping set-ups to discourage sex among the athletes.\", \"from\": 1736, \"to\": 2046, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1784, \"end\": 1791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\", \"score\": 0.8163406958745995, \"rank\": 0.19072027854433118, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\"}, {\"begin\": 1808, \"end\": 1818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Wanger\", \"score\": 0.9999918975614414, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ben Wanger\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Wanger\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Wanger\"}, {\"begin\": 1843, \"end\": 1849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2135115640487438e-37, \"text\": \"TikTok\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.